<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000i and 9000i - RADIATOR, REMOVE AND REPLACE - RADIATOR AND
        COMPONENT REMOVal - SURGE TANK
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>SURGE TANK</title>
        <para>The surge tank on the 3200 model, 4000 series, and 8500 model vehicle is located on the radiator frame
            driver side.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check tank for coolant; drain if necessary.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect harness connection to sensor and remove hose clamp securing overflow tube from
                surge tank. Disconnect overflow tube (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200806">Item 1, Figure 6</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200806" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200806.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200806.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="272px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Overflow Tube Remove</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. OVERFLOW OUTLET</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SURGE TANK</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove lower surge tank mounting bolts from driver side radiator frame (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200807">Item 2, Figure 7</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200807" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200807.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200807.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="272px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Surge Tank Lower Mounting Bolts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SURGE TANK</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SURGE TANK LOWER MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the upper surge tank mounting bolts from the radiator top frame (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200808">Item 1, Figure 8</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200808" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200808.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200808.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Surge Tank Upper Mounting Bolts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SURGE TANK TOP MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SURGE TANK</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove surge tank.</para>
            <figure id="f1200809" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200809.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200809.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Surge Tank Removal</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
